FBIS3-23348 "jptot013__l94029" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 24 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA MEXICO `Pacifist' Writer Arrested for Killing Candidate Colosio Preliminary Findings PA2403143494 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Mar 94 PA2403143494 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Mar 94 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] [Excerpts] Raul Sanchez Carrizo reports that two people have been arrested in connection with the killing of Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI] presidential candidate Luis Donaldo Colosio. You have already seen the two assassins on your TV screens. One of them is Mario Aburto Martinez. He is 23. There are two alleged killers. They are already under arrest. One of them fired at the PRI candidate. He is on screen right now. [video shows recorded footage of suspect being wrestled to the ground by angry members of a crowd; video also shows suspect being led away as members of a surrounding crowd punch him and pull his hair] He is Mario Aburto Martinez. He is 23. [passage omitted] He said he is the author of pacifist books that he has already delivered to the foreign media. Amid a great deal of secrecy, the Federal Attorney General's Office is also interrogating Vicente Mayoral Valenzuela, a man arrested as a witness [testigo]. Mayoral Valenzuela is also from the border city of Tijuana. Attorney General Diego Valadez has been in that city since last night.
